WEBVTT

00:06.047 --> 00:07.549
[pop music playing]

00:15.140 --> 00:18.601
-Humidity and freshly washed hair.
-Looks gorgeous on you.

00:18.685 --> 00:21.646
Everyone's got hats on.
I've got my hair up.

00:21.730 --> 00:24.649
That means that you can tell
it is nasty outside.

00:24.733 --> 00:26.901
-I'm not letting it frizz my hair.
-Me either.

00:26.985 --> 00:29.362
It's so rainy. It's gloomy and stuff.

00:29.446 --> 00:31.740
A good opportunity for a dossier.

00:31.823 --> 00:32.907
Yeah.

00:33.450 --> 00:37.746
So, this week,
we have Leonardo Loria Rico, a.k.a. Leo.

00:37.829 --> 00:39.956
-Cute.
-Beer.

00:43.084 --> 00:47.672
I make whatever you want me to make.
I'll make it special. I'll put love.

00:48.089 --> 00:53.803
The first time I met Leo,
we worked at the same restaurant.

00:53.887 --> 00:55.972
[chuckles] We used to flirt a lot.

00:56.056 --> 00:59.309
He never thought he was gonna get married,
have kids.

00:59.392 --> 01:02.228
Been married for six years,
have two boys,

01:02.437 --> 01:06.232
and Leo turned into a better father
than I imagined.

01:06.316 --> 01:11.571
But I am nominating Leo
because he is a ginormous slob.

01:11.654 --> 01:15.617
-He just leaves his stuff everywhere.
-[Leo] I'm very bachelor-style.

01:15.700 --> 01:18.620
I feel like I'm picking up
after three children.

01:18.703 --> 01:22.582
I tend to do things my way,
which is, like, sloppy.

01:22.916 --> 01:26.628
That drives me crazy.
He doesn't have a stereotypical adult job.

01:26.711 --> 01:30.423
I'm used to being the late-night person.
I'm like a vampire.

01:30.507 --> 01:33.176
[Bethany] Every night,
he's bringing bar food home.

01:33.259 --> 01:36.971
Chances are, you open the fridge,
there's going to be leftovers.

01:37.055 --> 01:41.351
There's only so many days in a row
I can eat Tater Tots reheated.

01:41.434 --> 01:46.064
I really wish he would cook more
because, I mean, he's good at it.

01:46.898 --> 01:48.066
-Hi, honey.
-Hey.

01:48.691 --> 01:54.072
When I look at Leo, I see a sexy beast,
but I never see him look past a mirror.

01:54.155 --> 01:57.075
All right, "Hey, sexy."
I'd love to see that.

01:57.492 --> 02:00.995
[Leo] When people look at me,
I can tell if they don't like me.

02:01.079 --> 02:05.125
What I show to people
sometimes might not be the full me.

02:05.750 --> 02:08.044
[Antoni]
Leo has an important event this week.

02:08.128 --> 02:11.714
He's gonna be attending his first
Parent-Teacher Mixer with Bethany.

02:11.798 --> 02:15.426
Leo's uncomfortable around other dads
and worries he's being judged.

02:15.510 --> 02:18.555
Ugh. I know that feeling.
When I got my kids, they were like:

02:18.638 --> 02:21.432
"Are you the big brother?
Are you gonna be a good parent?"

02:21.516 --> 02:24.102
-I was like, "Don't judge me."
-Mind your business.

02:24.185 --> 02:26.771
[Bethany] I think he believes
others are judging him,

02:26.855 --> 02:30.525
-so he judges himself.
-I don't have a lot of parent friends.

02:30.942 --> 02:33.153
[Bethany]
I'd love to have some joint friends,

02:33.236 --> 02:36.281
but it's like pulling teeth to get him
to socialize with others.

02:36.364 --> 02:38.950
It's that fear that I won't be accepted.

02:39.367 --> 02:42.829
I'd really love to see him take
his bartender personality

02:42.912 --> 02:45.206
and use that in social situations.

02:45.290 --> 02:49.919
And I wish when he went into school
with the kids, he could hold his head high

02:50.003 --> 02:54.716
because he is an amazing husband
and father, and he's providing for us.

02:55.174 --> 02:59.053
She thinks I have potential
for a better self. Ha!

02:59.137 --> 03:01.180
What's our mission, honey?

03:01.264 --> 03:04.767
Let's show this married bachelor
that he's a rad dad.

03:04.851 --> 03:06.686
Yeah.

03:06.769 --> 03:09.939
[Widelife's "All Things
(Just Keep Getting Better)" playing]

03:10.023 --> 03:13.568
♪ All things just keep getting better ♪

03:17.530 --> 03:19.866
♪ All your friends just hate me
Don't they? ♪

03:19.949 --> 03:21.743
♪ But I really don't care ♪

03:21.826 --> 03:25.204
It's raining. Need my umbrella.
There an umbrella that matches my outfit?

03:25.288 --> 03:26.205
Let's do this.

03:26.289 --> 03:28.124
Here's one that matches your outfit.

03:28.207 --> 03:30.043
-It's raining.
-[Antoni] You snooze, you lose.

03:30.960 --> 03:32.462
Keep those hats on.

03:32.545 --> 03:34.756
[Jonathan] Don't slip.
Don't hurt yourself.

03:34.839 --> 03:37.425
[Karamo] I wasn't planning on it.
That's why I got an umbrella.

03:37.508 --> 03:39.719
[Jonathan] Knock, knock, knock, I'm here.

03:40.803 --> 03:43.598
-Wait-- Hi.
-Hi.

03:43.681 --> 03:45.433
Nice to meet you. Can I hug you?

03:45.516 --> 03:47.769
-I'm Tan. Nice to meet you.
-How are you?

03:47.852 --> 03:49.395
-Antoni.
-Nice to meet you.

03:49.479 --> 03:51.105
Bobby. Great to meet you.

03:51.189 --> 03:52.398
-Thanks for having us.
-I'm Karamo.

03:52.482 --> 03:55.526
You used to have a major chin strap.
It's growing in.

03:55.610 --> 03:58.571
-He's shy.
-Shy? He's a shy baby.

03:58.655 --> 04:01.699
Leo looks like Mexican Santa Claus,
but on the off-season.

04:01.783 --> 04:04.244
He doesn't care about Miss Claus.

04:04.327 --> 04:09.374
-He's just chilling until December comes.
-I see kids, kids, kids.

04:09.457 --> 04:11.125
-Kids everywhere.
-[Karamo] Kids here.

04:11.209 --> 04:12.752
-Where are the kids?
-In daycare.

04:12.835 --> 04:15.380
She works in the day,
I work during the night.

04:15.463 --> 04:18.299
Oh, wow.
This is, like, a super-fun kitchen.

04:18.383 --> 04:21.261
-We got leftovers.
-Will you make us something?

04:21.344 --> 04:23.554
[Antoni] I'm making a stir-fry
of the food here.

04:23.638 --> 04:25.765
These are healthy options, right?

04:25.848 --> 04:28.601
The mac and cheese, not so much.
There's rice with cheese.

04:28.685 --> 04:30.687
We have three things with cheese.

04:30.770 --> 04:32.855
-[Jonathan] Everyone loves cheese.
-Hey!

04:32.939 --> 04:36.401
I can't resist.
There's so much stuff in his fridge.

04:36.484 --> 04:39.862
You wanna throw it in a pan,
add cheese, see what happens.

04:39.946 --> 04:42.282
-Chef, what do you want, olive oil?
-[Antoni] Yes.

04:42.365 --> 04:43.825
It's the basil olive oil.

04:44.200 --> 04:47.412
There's no judgments from the Fab 5.
How do you say it in Spanish?

04:47.495 --> 04:49.372
[Leo and Karamo speaking Spanish]

04:52.000 --> 04:55.545
I've never seen so many utensils
and pans and pots.

04:55.628 --> 04:58.548
-I used to have this one here.
-No.

04:58.631 --> 05:02.844
I have friend that is so tall, he got
that like [shouts] I'm like, "Okay."

05:02.927 --> 05:05.555
Your accent is so gorgeous.

05:05.888 --> 05:08.850
You can totally narrate
going-to-sleep meditations.

05:08.933 --> 05:13.187
It's like, "Honey, take a few breaths."
And I'll be like, "Yes." You know?

05:13.271 --> 05:18.609
Leonardo Loria Rico.

05:19.110 --> 05:22.363
-My God, look what's in the microwave.
-[Leo] That's my lunch.

05:22.447 --> 05:24.991
-[Karamo] From where, the bar?
-Taste the goodness.

05:25.074 --> 05:26.576
-No. No.
-Do me a favor.

05:26.659 --> 05:29.037
Find your trash can and throw it away.

05:29.120 --> 05:31.789
-[Leo] Oh, man, but it's good stuff.
-[Karamo] Throw it away.

05:32.332 --> 05:35.126
You bring food from the bar?
Why don't you cook?

05:35.209 --> 05:37.670
We split it. It depends
how busy our week is.

05:37.754 --> 05:41.549
-I cook at least two times a week.
-Is that enough for your wife?

05:41.632 --> 05:44.802
-You think she'd like more support?
-[Leo] I like to cook.

05:44.886 --> 05:48.264
Having the dinner ready for her
would be a lot better.

05:48.347 --> 05:52.143
-Can I see your closet?
-Sure, Tan, I've got this. No problem.

05:52.226 --> 05:53.644
[Karamo] I love the kiddie gate.

05:53.728 --> 05:55.938
We need one for Jonathan.

05:56.022 --> 05:57.440
Why would he not make the bed?

05:57.523 --> 05:59.817
And look how gross and un-fresh
those sheets look.

05:59.901 --> 06:03.821
-Oh, look at the closet.
-A walk-in closet. Good for them.

06:03.905 --> 06:07.742
-It's like a-- It's so-- [laughs]
-Uninviting.

06:09.368 --> 06:10.912
Okay, these are all shoe--

06:11.788 --> 06:12.872
Okay.

06:12.955 --> 06:16.626
Literally 20 percent of this space
is devoted to DVDs and CDs.

06:16.709 --> 06:18.711
They need to learn what streaming is.

06:19.128 --> 06:23.007
-Oh, my God.
-Oh, I don't like touching dead stuff.

06:23.091 --> 06:24.675
[both shouting and laughing]

06:24.967 --> 06:27.678
-[Tan] This is literally it.
-This is the closet?

06:27.762 --> 06:29.972
He doesn't have any clothes, though.

06:30.431 --> 06:32.850
-Oh, T-shirts.
-T-shirts.

06:33.184 --> 06:34.936
All right, no, no.

06:35.019 --> 06:37.313
-Is anything salvageable?
-There's nothing.

06:37.396 --> 06:42.985
Leo has logo tees, logo tees, logo tees,
and more logo tees.

06:43.069 --> 06:44.654
He needs help more than most.

06:45.071 --> 06:46.739
[Jonathan]
Child safety locks, that's good.

06:46.823 --> 06:48.950
Child safety locks,
but there's a hammer.

06:49.033 --> 06:51.953
-Like...
-That does not make sense. Nope.

06:52.036 --> 06:53.412
[shouting]

06:55.289 --> 06:59.043
-The kids and the gays can't get in.
-How do you not know how to get in that?

06:59.127 --> 07:00.920
I do know how to get in there.

07:01.671 --> 07:03.339
I might have broken it.

07:03.422 --> 07:05.675
[Tan] You know when you worried
you were a terrible father?

07:05.758 --> 07:07.260
[Karamo] This is it?

07:07.635 --> 07:09.971
[Antoni speaking in foreign language]

07:10.054 --> 07:13.349
[Antoni] So, this is everything-
but-the-kitchen-sink stir-fry.

07:13.683 --> 07:16.477
-Um... What is that?
-[Antoni] Four types of pasta

07:16.561 --> 07:20.231
that I found in your fridge
with two containers of peas.

07:20.314 --> 07:21.482
It's good.

07:23.568 --> 07:24.735
[laughing]

07:24.902 --> 07:27.321
You know, I'm a vegetarian.

07:27.405 --> 07:29.365
[Jonathan]
You're not veggie. You're a liar.

07:30.283 --> 07:33.244
-[Antoni] What's your favorite food?
-Typical pasta.

07:33.327 --> 07:34.996
Have you ever tasted fresh pasta?

07:35.079 --> 07:38.082
-No. We've been trying to get pasta--
-Leo.

07:38.166 --> 07:40.042
Italian food, what I like about it,

07:40.126 --> 07:43.588
it's a large dish in the center
everybody gets to go after.

07:43.671 --> 07:46.132
If you're having dinner with her,
it's romantic.

07:46.215 --> 07:48.301
And she likes wine,
so I don't have to worry.

07:48.384 --> 07:49.552
Perfect.

07:49.635 --> 07:51.387
[Tan] You leave your underwear
on the stairs?

07:51.471 --> 07:53.431
Yeah, I feel like a bachelor,

07:53.514 --> 07:55.766
wifey is always at war with the kids.

07:55.850 --> 07:58.811
-Yes.
-I'm pretty much with shorts downstairs.

07:58.895 --> 08:02.106
-Sometimes, I just wear my underwear.
-You're gross.

08:02.190 --> 08:05.151
A lot of the T-shirts
in your drawer are sloppy.

08:05.234 --> 08:06.527
I don't mind this one.

08:06.611 --> 08:09.614
If you were to dress this up,
wear some nice jeans,

08:09.697 --> 08:12.450
nice shoes, a jacket,
I can make that work.

08:12.909 --> 08:16.913
However, a lot of them look
like you've worn them 1,000 times.

08:16.996 --> 08:18.581
They look like student clothes.

08:18.664 --> 08:22.585
-It's clothing, who cares?
-I can't believe that you don't care.

08:23.085 --> 08:26.506
I wanna get you to the point
where Bethany says:

08:26.589 --> 08:29.717
"Leo's my guy. And look at him,
he looks fantastic."

08:29.800 --> 08:32.887
-We need to step it up.
-I'm very simple in clothing.

08:32.970 --> 08:36.140
I think about that when we go back
into the pictures.

08:36.224 --> 08:39.060
In all the pictures,
I have the same clothing.

08:39.143 --> 08:40.603
This isn't doing you favors.

08:40.686 --> 08:43.189
I wanna get you
to where you've got options

08:43.272 --> 08:46.984
that slim you down, make you feel
confident, make you feel dressed up.

08:47.693 --> 08:50.488
[singing]

08:51.739 --> 08:53.991
Welcome to my office. It's gorgeous.

08:54.075 --> 08:56.160
-It's nice. Ooh.
-Very convenient.

08:56.452 --> 08:59.372
-[Leo] My claws?
-What's going on there?

08:59.455 --> 09:02.208
Uh... I don't cut my nails that often.

09:02.291 --> 09:05.586
You could climb a tree with those
toenails. We gotta deal with that.

09:05.670 --> 09:09.048
When you look in the mirror,
do you like the way you look?

09:09.131 --> 09:12.718
Sometimes I got problems
with my hair on the sides.

09:12.802 --> 09:14.971
-It gets sloppy and horrible.
-Yeah.

09:15.054 --> 09:17.598
Having it too long is too much
of a hassle.

09:17.682 --> 09:19.976
How do you feel
when you're not in the bar?

09:20.059 --> 09:23.437
Does it make you feel
like people judge you in some way?

09:23.521 --> 09:26.524
-I think they do.
-I think you're an attractive man.

09:26.607 --> 09:30.194
But by just, like,
doing a couple of things here and there,

09:30.278 --> 09:34.198
it will up your confidence,
so that you do feel more comfortable.

09:34.699 --> 09:38.286
We don't have that much storage.
The storage I have is weird.

09:38.369 --> 09:41.747
They're big cabinets,
but I cannot put small stuff.

09:41.831 --> 09:44.166
-So, you need more storage?
-Yeah.

09:44.250 --> 09:46.877
The living room is where we spend
most of our time.

09:46.961 --> 09:48.045
Why is it red?

09:48.129 --> 09:52.008
I was gonna paint all these walls red,
so I started here, then I didn't finish.

09:52.091 --> 09:52.925
[Bobby] Okay, good.

09:53.009 --> 09:54.385
[both laughing]

09:54.468 --> 09:57.263
Red actually is a color
that makes you anxious.

09:57.346 --> 10:00.683
So, blues, grays,
those are more soothing, happy colors.

10:00.766 --> 10:03.728
This isn't the best layout for this room.

10:03.811 --> 10:07.648
Somebody told me not to put
in a corner a TV, the layout is weird.

10:07.732 --> 10:09.609
I was like, "I want it there."

10:14.030 --> 10:16.365
[Karamo]
So, you have a big event at the school?

10:16.449 --> 10:20.036
They do these Parent-Teacher Mixers.

10:20.119 --> 10:24.040
And every time, I say no.
I find an excuse like, "I have to work."

10:24.123 --> 10:26.292
-Got it.
-Wifey was like, "No, not this time."

10:26.375 --> 10:28.377
What's your relationship with the others?

10:28.461 --> 10:31.839
-Nonexistent. [laughs]
-Nonexistent. Why's that?

10:31.922 --> 10:35.718
I definitely felt that, you know,
just the glances sometimes.

10:35.801 --> 10:38.929
And I'm a bartender.
I think people prejudge me.

10:39.013 --> 10:40.765
It doesn't make me feel good.

10:41.390 --> 10:43.267
Wifey encourages that I call the dads

10:43.351 --> 10:46.979
and like, "You wanna bring the kid here?
Maybe they could play together."

10:47.063 --> 10:50.358
I have a feeling that if I did that,
it would benefit me,

10:50.441 --> 10:52.193
and my kids and wife would be happy.

10:52.568 --> 10:55.321
I want to make more time for them
that I don't right now.

10:55.404 --> 10:57.948
-Why are you getting emotional?
-I love my kids.

11:03.496 --> 11:05.122
And I want to be with them.

11:07.333 --> 11:08.959
They mean everything to me.

11:09.960 --> 11:11.921
I can tell you're a great father.

11:12.505 --> 11:15.758
It's just figuring out those ways
around the fear.

11:15.841 --> 11:19.470
Hanging out with other dads
who understand what you're feeling

11:19.553 --> 11:22.264
gives you an opportunity
to hang with the kids,

11:22.348 --> 11:25.393
but also relieve the stress
and guilt you're feeling

11:25.476 --> 11:28.896
-that you're not doing enough.
-I want to change something.

11:29.397 --> 11:32.942
Or not to change,
but I call it "evolve part of your life."

11:33.025 --> 11:37.613
That's exactly it.
You have to know how to evolve.

11:37.696 --> 11:39.824
-I have to know that.
-That is phenomenal.

11:39.907 --> 11:41.450
[Jonathan] Hey, guys, catch me.

11:42.243 --> 11:43.202
Just kidding.

11:44.036 --> 11:48.040
I got a little tense for a second
or emotional, so to speak.

11:48.833 --> 11:51.377
-I'm scared.
-We'll be gentle.

11:51.460 --> 11:52.461
Please.

11:52.545 --> 11:55.798
Your wife, Bethany, told us
that you are her sexy man.

11:55.881 --> 11:58.008
-She said sexy beast.
-Sexy beast.

11:58.092 --> 12:01.137
Anytime a woman calls you a sexy beast,
you gotta hit your chest.

12:01.220 --> 12:02.930
-I do the dance.
-What's the dance?

12:03.013 --> 12:05.349
-Oh, no, it's the dance.
-No, you dance.

12:05.975 --> 12:07.893
-All right.
-That's your game?

12:08.894 --> 12:10.479
Oh, yeah, baby, come on.

12:10.563 --> 12:12.106
[pop music playing]

12:20.531 --> 12:22.491
[Antoni] Leo is passionate about food,

12:22.575 --> 12:26.078
and I want Leo to prepare meals
for his wife and kids

12:26.162 --> 12:29.498
that they can have when they come home,
and everything is ready.

12:29.582 --> 12:31.584
[Bobby] I wanna make sure
I show Leo and Bethany,

12:31.667 --> 12:34.879
don't let the kids take over
every aspect of your home.

12:34.962 --> 12:37.006
Everyone needs to have
that place to chill,

12:37.089 --> 12:39.675
and when there's chaos everywhere,
you can't chill.

12:40.259 --> 12:42.803
[Jonathan] He's an attractive, lovely man.

12:42.887 --> 12:45.931
We can polish him up,
and we can turn him out a bit.

12:46.015 --> 12:47.725
We just need to unleash it.

12:52.188 --> 12:56.775
Leo is truly living like a bachelor.
All I see is college student, single guy.

12:56.859 --> 12:59.320
A guy who hangs out
at a bar every night.

12:59.403 --> 13:01.113
We need to step it up.

13:01.530 --> 13:05.034
My hope is that Leo can get
his dad groove back.

13:05.117 --> 13:08.454
Where he feels really cool
about being a dad.

13:13.292 --> 13:15.377
-[Tan] All right, ready for this?
-[Leo] I am.

13:15.461 --> 13:18.380
I'm about to open my eyes
to something different.

13:18.464 --> 13:20.925
-A little bit nervous? [laughs]
-Yes.

13:21.008 --> 13:24.929
I've been into this store many a time.
It's one of my favorites

13:25.012 --> 13:28.807
for somebody who, uh, is slightly taller,
and you've got proportions

13:28.891 --> 13:31.894
that do require a store
that has larger options.

13:31.977 --> 13:32.853
Mm-hm.

13:32.937 --> 13:35.898
What parts do you love about your body,
and what parts do you think:

13:35.981 --> 13:40.110
-"I don't wanna highlight"?
-Well, I like my shoulders and my legs,

13:40.194 --> 13:43.364
-but I don't like the muffin top.
-We all got it.

13:43.781 --> 13:47.952
I wanna concentrate on a slimmer fit that
will give you a nicer look to your leg.

13:48.536 --> 13:52.206
If you wear a wide leg,
you're just gonna look short and big.

13:52.289 --> 13:55.501
These are jeans that are soft,
it's not actually denim.

13:55.584 --> 13:58.671
You like comfort, so I wanna go
with something that has stretch.

13:58.754 --> 14:01.757
I've noticed that, too.
That stretch is comfortable.

14:02.633 --> 14:07.263
[Tan] We've got the Parent-Teacher Mixer.
Something like a blazer could be great.

14:07.680 --> 14:12.059
I always liked blazers, but I've never
found one I like that would fit me.

14:12.142 --> 14:16.313
You can wear it with jeans,
with trousers, with sneakers, with a boot.

14:16.397 --> 14:18.023
I love a simple polka dot.

14:18.107 --> 14:22.069
As opposed to going for the printed tee,
go for a printed shirt.

14:22.152 --> 14:24.905
-Shoes.
-I'm a big guy, I step hard.

14:24.989 --> 14:29.159
I'd really want to find a shoe
that's gonna be strong and comfortable.

14:29.243 --> 14:31.370
That will last more than six months.

14:31.453 --> 14:35.249
Get your shoes from a place like this,
they have a wider foot.

14:35.332 --> 14:38.252
It's gonna accommodate your foot
the way you need.

14:38.335 --> 14:41.589
I get that Leo's daunted
by being around other fathers,

14:41.672 --> 14:44.508
and if I were dressed that way,
I would, too.

14:44.592 --> 14:47.761
I want him to feel confident,
secure and empowered

14:47.845 --> 14:49.221
meeting these fathers.

14:49.805 --> 14:52.141
Let's take a look. Whoo!

14:52.433 --> 14:55.603
Let's add in a little bit of style.

14:55.686 --> 14:58.564
I'm gonna roll these sleeves
a couple of times.

14:58.647 --> 15:00.691
A better version of casual?

15:00.774 --> 15:03.777
Yeah. I think it could be more formal
like a parent.

15:03.861 --> 15:08.032
'Cause sometimes they see me
as the older brother picking up the kids.

15:08.115 --> 15:10.409
It's gonna give you a shape you want.

15:10.492 --> 15:13.495
I've given you a shorter jacket
than the T-shirt.

15:13.579 --> 15:18.500
We're mixing the proportions, so not only
do you focus on your slim parts,

15:18.584 --> 15:21.295
you don't focus on the parts
you don't want to focus on.

15:21.378 --> 15:23.088
They're not noticing that.

15:23.172 --> 15:26.634
It doesn't show me like a big guy.
More like a comfortable person.

15:26.717 --> 15:30.220
Yeah. I want you to start
to realize you don't need to wear

15:30.304 --> 15:33.599
those shorts and T-shirts.
Feel comfortable in this.

15:33.682 --> 15:37.186
Men have body issues.
We are as insecure as women are.

15:37.269 --> 15:39.813
We just don't talk about it comfortably.

15:39.897 --> 15:43.067
I want it to be a real conversation
we can all have.

15:43.150 --> 15:45.819
Okay, great. Come on. This is gonna work.

15:45.903 --> 15:48.530
These jeans are made
for super-tall people.

15:48.614 --> 15:50.491
-We'll have them altered.
-Okay.

15:50.574 --> 15:53.786
I don't want it to be too high.
Slip this on for me.

15:53.869 --> 15:55.329
-Okay.
-Yeah.

15:56.205 --> 16:00.417
Look in the mirror. Tell me
what you're seeing, feeling and thinking.

16:00.501 --> 16:03.671
-I see a stud. [laughs]
-You see a stud?

16:04.171 --> 16:07.800
I love that the suit is fitted.
It's nice and slim.

16:08.217 --> 16:11.345
The fact that it just about closes,
I want that.

16:11.428 --> 16:13.931
If it's too roomy,
it's not the right size.

16:14.014 --> 16:16.141
Okay. I thought it was the opposite.

16:16.225 --> 16:18.852
You'll look
like you're drowning in the suit.

16:18.936 --> 16:22.398
So, I want you to keep it open.
It gives you a nice line.

16:22.481 --> 16:24.400
That's taking 20 pounds off you.

16:24.483 --> 16:27.194
If you close that,
it would highlight your stomach.

16:27.277 --> 16:29.238
Also, we've tucked in your shirt.

16:29.321 --> 16:33.534
If I leave it open, and it hangs down,
you'll look bigger and shorter.

16:33.617 --> 16:35.244
-Yeah.
-You don't want that.

16:35.327 --> 16:37.579
I think I feel comfortable
going out in this.

16:37.663 --> 16:39.707
You look appropriate for your age.

16:39.790 --> 16:41.667
You look like a rad dad.

16:48.507 --> 16:52.469
The biggest problem in Leo's house,
it's more a nursery than a home.

16:52.553 --> 16:54.346
The kids' stuff, it's everywhere.

16:54.430 --> 16:56.765
And Daddy's toys
all over the place as well.

16:56.849 --> 17:01.353
So, I wanna make storage spaces
the boys can use and the adults can use.

17:01.437 --> 17:03.981
We have to cover up the air conditioning.

17:04.064 --> 17:07.317
We need to put a vent
at the front of this, at an angle.

17:07.401 --> 17:09.486
-Yeah.
-I know you've always got it.

17:09.570 --> 17:10.904
-All right.
-Thank you.

17:12.197 --> 17:14.616
Living room, living room.

17:14.700 --> 17:16.535
Put your back into it, man.

17:23.375 --> 17:25.919
What we're doing
is, uh, we're going traditional.

17:26.003 --> 17:27.713
-Okay.
-Super old-school.

17:27.796 --> 17:30.174
[speaking in Italian]

17:30.340 --> 17:32.426
-Good evening. Good to see you.
-How are you?

17:32.509 --> 17:34.595
-Nice to meet you.
-Leo, this is Riccardo.

17:34.678 --> 17:36.889
I love traditional Italian food.

17:36.972 --> 17:40.184
There is no place better.
So, I'm excited to be here.

17:40.267 --> 17:42.269
Will you teach us how to make fresh pasta?

17:42.352 --> 17:44.396
-We've got to get you an apron.
-Me, too?

17:44.480 --> 17:46.774
-You don't get anything. [laughs]
-Okay.

17:47.191 --> 17:49.651
Somebody who loves Italian food
the way Leo does,

17:49.735 --> 17:54.823
he's the perfect candidate for me
to preach the fresh pasta gospel to.

17:54.907 --> 17:58.577
To mix the dough, we're gonna do it
with the well system.

17:58.660 --> 18:02.039
Make a well, crack the egg,
put it in the middle. There.

18:02.998 --> 18:06.752
The slower you mix,
the more flour is gonna get incorporated.

18:06.835 --> 18:08.879
Just making scrambled eggs.

18:08.962 --> 18:10.881
See how it's coming into a ball?

18:10.964 --> 18:13.509
It's not like a pastry dough
you can overwork.

18:13.592 --> 18:15.385
You're never gonna overwork this.

18:15.469 --> 18:17.846
[Antoni] Fresh pasta,
it's just so delicate.

18:17.930 --> 18:22.684
It's so easy to make. Anybody can make it.
It's better than reheating bar food.

18:23.143 --> 18:25.729
[Riccardo] Put it like this,
and squeeze it through.

18:25.813 --> 18:27.689
[Antoni] It's the right amount of flour.

18:27.773 --> 18:30.609
Put it through until the clumps are gone.

18:30.692 --> 18:32.528
-One more time.
-A couple times.

18:32.611 --> 18:35.405
-Like I'm touching chewing gum.
-Yeah.

18:35.989 --> 18:38.700
-Other way. You wanna go this way.
-Other way?

18:38.784 --> 18:41.453
-Criss-crossing.
-You do a 90-degree shift.

18:41.912 --> 18:43.288
[Riccardo] Then you stretch it.

18:43.372 --> 18:46.458
We make it a bit shorter
because we wanna discourage

18:46.542 --> 18:48.210
-eating pasta with spoons.
-I agree.

18:48.293 --> 18:50.379
-Well, is that a thing?
-Not for me.

18:51.380 --> 18:52.631
It's better to slurp.

18:52.714 --> 18:54.591
-Exactly.
-That's the fun of it.

18:54.675 --> 18:57.010
You feed it through here, pull it through.

18:57.094 --> 18:59.221
-[Antoni] That's so beautiful.
-[Leo] That's is so--

18:59.304 --> 19:00.931
-[Antoni] It is like angel hair.
-It is.

19:01.014 --> 19:02.850
You just shocked my world.

19:02.933 --> 19:05.769
I always have the idea
that there was so many things to do

19:05.853 --> 19:07.688
before getting to this process.

19:07.771 --> 19:10.482
-Then straight to the--
-[Riccardo] Straight to the water.

19:10.566 --> 19:12.609
[Antoni] Fresh pasta is so good for kids,
too.

19:12.693 --> 19:16.029
You know, my mom used to do butter,
parmesan and ketchup.

19:16.113 --> 19:17.739
-And ketchup?
-In Italy.

19:17.823 --> 19:19.199
It adds sweetness.

19:19.283 --> 19:22.161
No, there's nothing wrong with that
as long as it tastes good.

19:22.244 --> 19:23.829
Let's cook, and let's eat.

19:24.580 --> 19:27.124
You mentioned you cook dinner
twice a week.

19:27.207 --> 19:28.834
Twice a week. Monday's off.

19:28.917 --> 19:31.378
I have time
to set everything into motion.

19:31.461 --> 19:33.839
If you're planning a dinner
on a work night,

19:33.922 --> 19:36.717
your wife comes home
and sees fresh pasta there,

19:36.800 --> 19:39.845
all she has to do is boil water,
throw the pasta in,

19:39.928 --> 19:43.265
-and heat up a sauce that you made.
-That'd be fantastic.

19:43.348 --> 19:45.601
It's romantic.
It's showing up for your family.

19:45.684 --> 19:47.769
-It's interesting.
-Good challenge.

19:47.853 --> 19:50.272
I wanna make something
that they'll be like, "Wow."

19:50.731 --> 19:51.773
-[Riccardo] Gentlemen.
-Yes.

19:51.857 --> 19:53.358
This is a tagliolini.

19:53.442 --> 19:56.612
Now, this is as simple
as a tomato sauce gets.

19:56.695 --> 20:01.992
Nothing is cooked. It is olive oil,
heirloom tomatoes, basil and wild oregano.

20:02.075 --> 20:03.202
[Leo] It looks so great.

20:03.285 --> 20:05.245
[Riccardo &amp; Antoni speaking in Italian]

20:05.329 --> 20:07.539
-Sorry, can we have a spoon, please?
-[laughing]

20:09.666 --> 20:11.543
-This is fabulous.
-Right?

20:11.627 --> 20:15.422
-And it is so simple.
-It is. If you make these in the morning,

20:15.505 --> 20:17.674
let them sit out
at room temperature covered,

20:17.758 --> 20:20.385
it's perfect,
the flavors will come together.

20:20.469 --> 20:24.306
-I'll dream about this tonight.
-Thank you. It was a pleasure.

20:28.060 --> 20:30.395
-I got you. Yeah.
-Thank you.

20:30.854 --> 20:32.606
-Yeah.
-Daddy.

20:33.440 --> 20:35.651
-Give me five.
-Let's dance.

20:35.984 --> 20:38.654
There's some new kids coming in.
Wanna say hi?

20:38.737 --> 20:40.405
-Hey.
-What?

20:40.489 --> 20:44.576
Look, that's Anne Marie, that's Lulu,
that's Genevieve.

20:44.660 --> 20:46.370
All your little friends.

20:46.453 --> 20:49.081
[Karamo] I invited some dads
from your kids' school

20:49.164 --> 20:52.334
because this is a spot
where you can bond, have fun,

20:52.417 --> 20:55.837
enjoy the kids, enjoy the fathers
at a daddy play date.

20:55.921 --> 20:57.547
-What's up, Dad?
-What's up?

20:59.174 --> 21:01.176
[man] Girls, you need to come over here.

21:03.053 --> 21:05.013
Watch that guy. A future CEO.

21:05.097 --> 21:07.474
[man] He could be talking to my wife.

21:07.557 --> 21:08.850
[laughing]

21:10.102 --> 21:12.020
When were you last around fathers?

21:12.104 --> 21:14.398
It's the first time
I've met more than two.

21:14.481 --> 21:16.900
-Today is the first day you--?
-[Leo] Seriously.

21:16.984 --> 21:20.153
The greatest thing for me
when I got the kids was to make sure

21:20.237 --> 21:23.031
that I started to interact
with other dads immediately.

21:23.115 --> 21:25.784
We just could connect,
you just have some fun.

21:25.867 --> 21:28.495
It's a great way
for you to support the kids.

21:28.829 --> 21:30.330
Meet around, mingle.

21:31.331 --> 21:33.458
-Guys, wanna gather around?
-[Leo] All right.

21:33.542 --> 21:36.378
-Scott. Nice to meet you.
-Leo. Nice to meet you.

21:36.795 --> 21:40.215
[Karamo] The fact that Leo is nervous
about not fitting in, I understand.

21:40.299 --> 21:43.844
But I want him to know
that he can be relaxed, be confident.

21:43.927 --> 21:46.930
-You've got this, boo.
-Say hi.

21:47.347 --> 21:48.890
I love your hair, man.

21:48.974 --> 21:50.892
He had that much hair
when he was born.

21:50.976 --> 21:51.977
-Yeah?
-Yeah.

21:52.519 --> 21:55.772
I'll sit in an airport
and watch other people with kids

21:55.856 --> 21:59.026
quietly reading books, and mine
are running around like banshees.

21:59.484 --> 22:03.405
He knows what's going on, yeah.
Oh, no, here's the child. Take him.

22:04.406 --> 22:07.200
[Karamo] He was worried
everyone was gonna be staring at him

22:07.284 --> 22:10.370
and judging. He needed a push
in the right direction.

22:10.454 --> 22:14.166
Hey, kids, you guys ready to dance?
Friend, wanna dance with me?

22:14.958 --> 22:18.253
I want you to cross your arms,
and you're gonna lean with it.

22:18.337 --> 22:21.757
Look at you. You already look swagged out.
Look at this straight Fab 5.

22:21.840 --> 22:22.841
[laughing]

22:24.468 --> 22:28.096
Good job. I'm no longer sweet dad.
I'm cool dad.

22:28.597 --> 22:30.974
Yeah, lean with it. That's attitude.

22:31.058 --> 22:34.019
-Get it out.
-Now he's busting out the moves.

22:34.102 --> 22:35.937
That's a break dance, buddy.

22:36.021 --> 22:39.816
-We're looking goofy together.
-I love it. Thanks for that.

22:39.900 --> 22:40.776
Goofy is the word.

22:41.234 --> 22:44.654
[Karamo] I wanted Leo to understand
he's not alone in this journey,

22:44.738 --> 22:48.533
and that his kids are gonna be okay,
and that's all that matters.

22:48.617 --> 22:49.576
Nice job, guys.

22:49.659 --> 22:52.204
-Yeah.
-I'll hang out with you anytime.

22:52.287 --> 22:54.790
-Next time we'll play poker.
-Poker.

23:00.003 --> 23:02.839
This is our office. This is the lot.
I'm excited you're here. After you.

23:02.923 --> 23:04.591
-Okay.
-After you.

23:04.674 --> 23:06.301
I'm such a gentleman.

23:06.384 --> 23:08.178
-Bobby.
-Hello.

23:08.261 --> 23:09.262
How's it going?

23:09.346 --> 23:13.225
-Bobby, you're forever architecting.
-Working on something. Right now it's you.

23:13.934 --> 23:17.854
Let's take this down 'cause
we're just doing a big moment today.

23:17.938 --> 23:20.857
You've got
a major asymmetrical bob. Love it.

23:20.941 --> 23:22.567
I have a surprise for you.

23:22.943 --> 23:24.736
-We're doing pedicures, honey.
-Oh, wow.

23:25.362 --> 23:29.658
This is Tamika, this is Angelita.
We are going to have a little spa day.

23:29.741 --> 23:32.702
Once I saw those toes,
or talons as my mom would call them,

23:32.786 --> 23:35.622
I couldn't deal with your hair
until we got your feet sorted.

23:35.705 --> 23:37.916
Can you rest your feet
and get over here?

23:37.999 --> 23:40.794
-I'm doing all the things for you guys.
-Hello, ladies.

23:40.877 --> 23:43.213
-[Tamika] Ever had a pedicure before?
-One time.

23:43.296 --> 23:46.716
-How often do you clip your toenails?
-Every time they're going

23:46.800 --> 23:48.593
right above the other side.

23:48.677 --> 23:52.055
[Jonathan] Society and culture
doesn't teach men to do self-care.

23:52.139 --> 23:54.307
It's not girly, stupid or too much.

23:54.641 --> 23:57.060
It makes your toes look great,
and makes you relax.

23:57.561 --> 24:00.355
How often is right for a pedicure,
once a month?

24:00.438 --> 24:01.356
Definitely.

24:01.439 --> 24:03.441
I'm gonna do a little face mask
on you guys.

24:03.525 --> 24:06.736
-Ooh.
-[Jonathan] I'm a big fan of DIY masks.

24:06.820 --> 24:09.948
I took oats, and I ground them up
in a food processor,

24:10.031 --> 24:12.951
and this is manuka honey,
it promotes skin healing

24:13.034 --> 24:14.744
more than normal honey would.

24:14.828 --> 24:17.831
This is a great mixture to put on
before we shave

24:17.914 --> 24:19.332
or do any sort of skin stuff.

24:19.749 --> 24:22.169
The oats in this
are a gentle exfoliant.

24:22.586 --> 24:25.881
-Your turn.
-[Bobby] Mm. This tastes really good.

24:25.964 --> 24:29.593
-I am gonna try to kiss my wife like this.
-[Bobby] It's really good.

24:31.303 --> 24:32.512
-It is.
-[Bobby] Right?

24:33.138 --> 24:35.015
[Jonathan]
I'll just take this off of you.

24:36.141 --> 24:38.768
-My God, are you falling asleep, Leo?
-No.

24:38.852 --> 24:40.645
[laughing]

24:40.729 --> 24:43.273
So, okay, love it.
Are we done with our pedis?

24:43.356 --> 24:46.943
Look at that toe.
They're gonna be scratching nobody now.

24:47.569 --> 24:51.072
Bobby, look at your face.
It's radiant and moisturized.

24:51.156 --> 24:52.699
And your face, too.

24:52.782 --> 24:55.493
-Thank you so much. Come with me.
-Thank you.

24:56.703 --> 24:59.080
You can step into my gorgeous office.

25:00.707 --> 25:03.960
I'm just gonna clean up
the upper part of your cheek.

25:04.502 --> 25:06.922
And you don't wanna go too low.

25:07.005 --> 25:10.175
It's about working
with the beard you have, which I like.

25:10.258 --> 25:13.678
We're gonna taken your middle out,
and clean it up.

25:14.262 --> 25:17.599
For years, I thought
I was never gonna get a mustache.

25:17.682 --> 25:20.977
-But then you did? [laughing]
-It was like, "Yeah."

25:21.394 --> 25:23.605
I'll take it shorter on the sides
and the back,

25:23.688 --> 25:26.942
but leave length on top
so you can wear it curly.

25:27.025 --> 25:28.944
-[razor buzzing]
-Oh, gosh, she's so loud.

25:29.736 --> 25:31.905
Oh, she gets so angry.

25:32.405 --> 25:36.159
Oh, honey, right there, we can't--
She just gets so strong.

25:36.868 --> 25:40.288
After the conference,
if you accidentally knock your wife up,

25:40.372 --> 25:42.540
name the baby Jonathan.
It's my fault

25:42.624 --> 25:44.459
-because I got you his haircut.
-Funny.

25:44.542 --> 25:47.629
And if you have a girl,
it could be my last name with an A on it,

25:47.712 --> 25:50.840
Vanessa, which was also coincidentally
my drag name.

25:50.924 --> 25:54.135
-And it feels good. It's like, "Vanessa."
-Oh, my God.

25:54.219 --> 25:55.762
[both laughing]

25:55.845 --> 25:58.139
♪ Take on the world
Don't be afraid ♪

26:01.476 --> 26:05.021
-[Leo] You can make a carpet with my hair.
-The hair on the ground.

26:05.105 --> 26:07.565
[Jonathan] Bobby's collecting it
so he can do something with it.

26:07.649 --> 26:10.193
♪ Take on the world ♪

26:10.277 --> 26:11.778
[Jonathan] Confidence is sexy.

26:11.861 --> 26:14.239
I was loving the smile
that I had to work with,

26:14.322 --> 26:16.658
and I know this canvas
is willing to be molded,

26:16.741 --> 26:18.702
so I'm willing to make a masterpiece.

26:19.119 --> 26:22.998
Here's the new and improved Leo. Ba-da!

26:23.415 --> 26:25.709
-Hello, how are you doing?
-[laughing]

26:25.792 --> 26:27.210
-Do you like?
-I love it.

26:27.294 --> 26:29.212
-How do you feel?
-Feeling fresh.

26:29.296 --> 26:31.715
Get all up in there. Check yourself out.

26:31.798 --> 26:34.426
Look at that. I look so respectable.

26:34.509 --> 26:38.805
-Everyone will take you seriously.
-I just need my golden tooth like:

26:38.888 --> 26:41.850
Get out of here.
We can leave the golden tooth off.

26:41.933 --> 26:43.476
-Fine.
-This is perfect.

26:43.560 --> 26:45.812
-Give me a Mexico City kiss.
-Oh, yeah.

26:46.563 --> 26:48.940
-Isn't it three?
-Yeah, we'll make it four.

26:49.024 --> 26:51.651
-Oh. cuatro, honey.
-Cuatro.

26:51.735 --> 26:56.031
♪ I just wanna have fun ♪

26:56.114 --> 26:57.991
♪ Fun, fun, fun, fun ♪

26:58.450 --> 27:02.787
♪ So let your hair fall down
Today we do what we want ♪

27:02.871 --> 27:04.080
[Jonathan] Love.

27:05.749 --> 27:08.668
-Are you ready?
-Ready or not, it's happening.

27:08.752 --> 27:11.129
[in English accent] Remember
in primary school in South London

27:11.212 --> 27:12.714
where we used to do this?

27:12.797 --> 27:15.759
-We would play blocks.
-And talking with my blocks.

27:15.842 --> 27:18.011
-Then we'd do our German accent.
-[laughing]

27:18.094 --> 27:20.972
-[Truck horn honks]
-Oh, my God. He looks great.

27:21.848 --> 27:23.224
Come on in.

27:23.683 --> 27:25.518
-Welcome home!
-Whoa!

27:25.602 --> 27:28.646
-Oh, my God. Whose house is this?
-Yours.

27:31.900 --> 27:32.776
[Leo] Oh, wow.

27:35.153 --> 27:37.489
-Look at me.
-Oh, you've got goose bumps.

27:37.572 --> 27:39.908
-You've got goose bumps.
-Wow. Look at that.

27:40.575 --> 27:42.827
Your problem was your lack of storage.

27:42.911 --> 27:43.828
Yes.

27:43.912 --> 27:46.998
So, I added these bookcases.
From the waist down,

27:47.082 --> 27:51.711
you've got the boys' space.
Then waist up is family and Mom and Dad.

27:52.212 --> 27:54.547
That is amazing, Bobby.
None of us realized that,

27:54.631 --> 27:58.009
-and we were playing with the toys.
-[Antoni] This flip here with the sofa

27:58.093 --> 28:00.553
-makes it twice as wide.
-You can feel the space.

28:00.637 --> 28:03.473
I like, in a smaller space,
a glass coffee table.

28:03.556 --> 28:05.683
It makes the space feel bigger.

28:05.767 --> 28:06.810
[Fab 5] Aw...

28:08.645 --> 28:10.021
Ready to see some more?

28:11.022 --> 28:15.235
-Whoa. Everything is different.
-[Bobby] I built this bench.

28:15.318 --> 28:18.696
Now you can fit at least seven people
on just the bench.

28:18.780 --> 28:20.031
-We're good.
-Okay.

28:20.115 --> 28:21.616
[Jonathan] There's no wall there.

28:23.993 --> 28:26.204
[Leo] It's a different kitchen.
It looks so big.

28:26.287 --> 28:28.331
-[Bobby] Ready to see more?
-More? Come on.

28:28.415 --> 28:29.666
[all laughing]

